DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "contextCurrency.pl", "contextPercent.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("Currency")->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros => 1); $final = 90 + random(-30, 30, 0.05); $current = Currency($final); Context("Percent"); $decimal = random(0.16,0.20,0.01); $percent = Percent($decimal); Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(b => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("b + $decimal b = $final");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Read the scenario. Then write a complete sentence that defines a variable to use. Lastly, write an equation to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the equation.
The final bill at a restaurant one night was [`[$current]\text{,}`] including a [`[$percent]`] tip. What was the bill before the tip was added? Set up an equation to answer this question. There is no need to solve it.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|b|]* as the variable.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{20}
END_PGML
